Cross River State Commissioner for Health and Chairman COVID-19 State Task Force Response Team Dr. Betta Edu added another feather on her cap when she received another award of Excellence from the federal Ministry of women Affairs and Social Development. With the award, Edu’s name will be included among list of Nigeria Quintessential women’s roll call of fame. An inference drawn from the letter received by Edu from the those who awarded her with the award of honour/ recognition for her meritorious services to humanity reads;“ we appreciate your positive impact, relentless effort and diligence in your esteemed position which has distinguished you amongst so many women in Nigeria, it is highly commendable. The Federal Ministry of Women Affairs and Social Development in Collaboration with Excellent Women International have considered you worthy of recognition and endorsement in this year’s “THE NIGERIAN QUINTESSENTIAL WOMAN AWARD OF EXCELLENCE”. The letter also reads; “This is an annual noble award to encouraged women who have carved a niche for themselves through vision and positive impact in their respected positions and in the society. The letter further concluded, that Dr. Betta Edu will be recognised on July 30,few days to come, along side other top ranking Nigerian women of substance who may had distinguished themselves in their various fields of human endeavours.